"```sql\nSELECT DISTINCT account.account_id\nFROM account\nJOIN order ON account.account_id = order.account_id\nJOIN client ON account.account_id = disp.account_id\nJOIN disp ON client.client_id = disp.client_id\nJOIN district ON client.district_id = district.district_id\nWHERE order.k_symbol = 'SIPO' AND district.A2 = 'Pisek';\n```\n\nThis SQL query selects distinct account IDs from the `account` table that have placed orders for household payments (indicated by `k_symbol = 'SIPO'`) and are located in the district of Pisek. The query joins the necessary tables using the foreign key relationships to filter the accounts based on the specified conditions."